Acting City Manager Abala Wanga maintained that all the restructuring operations are meant for the envisaged development of the citySome of the structures said to have been built on top of sewer lines and road reserves. Kisumu county government has suspended the demolition of business kiosks owned by small-scale traders. 
This comes days after residents, civil society groups and some leaders complained about the move to destroy the livelihoods of the traders without giving them an alternative place to ply their trade.



