They also alleged that structures of some powerful people had been spared.
But acting City Manager Abala Wanga maintained that all the restructuring operations are meant for the envisaged development of the city as contained in Governor Peter Anyang’ Nyong’o’s development agenda.
“We appeal to Kisumu residents, especially traders ,to ignore a few people politicising the city restructuring operations. Some of these politicians don’t mean well for the progress of this county and have even been using money to incite some traders to stage demonstrations,” Mr Wanga said.



