The county has been removing illegal structures and extensions on residential government buildings within the town.
On top of sewer lines
Mr Wanga said some of the structures had been built on top of sewer lines and road reserves, giving an example of estates like Migosi. 
However, he noted that the demolition of the business kiosks has been suspended until Uhuru Business Park Complex, which is under construction, gets ready for occupation by the affected traders.
The city manager also indicated that the traders are being registered and will be given first priority at the Uhuru Business Park, which has a capacity of almost 10,000 ultra-modern stalls.



