He also warned county staff who have allocated themselves stalls at Chichwa market, ordering them to surrender them within a week for re-allocation to needy traders, or face disciplinary action.Traders who acquired more than one stall at Chichwa Market have also been directed to urgently surrender the excess, and adhere to the 'One trader, one stall policy'.“The county government values the traders and will do everything at its disposal to ensure they get alternative places to do business,” Mr Wanga said. The county administration, led by Governor Nyong’o, has also directed its attention to recovery of grabbed land in the county. It’s targeting 52 illegally acquired pieces of land.The city manager noted that some of the land parcels had been earmarked for public institutions and parking areas.“Currently, the county is in the process of recovering six of the plots. Four cases are in court. We wish to notify the public that the recovery process is three-pronged,” Mr Wanga said.Buildings on pathways, playgrounds and wetlands will be demolished after notices issued to owners expire.   Work had already started at more than 11 feeder ports on Lake Victoria but the activities later went silent. Beautification of the lakeside city expected to attract tourists and investors. Senior specialists among those affected. Kenya has secured its first 24 million doses of the vaccine through Covax. Keen to expand his support base, Dr Ruto, backed by his allies, has gone full-blown to challenge his main political opponents.